# 6. 夕暮れ時の出会い

Tsukasa: Anyway, everyone seemed to be very excited about their new situations!
Ichika: I see... I'm glad everyone at Kamiyama High's also enjoying things.
Saki: Toya and Mizuki being in the same class sounds like so much fun! I wish I could be their classmate!
Honami: But Shiho would be so sad if you left your current class.
Saki: No, you're right...! Then, I'll stay where I am♪
Shiho: *Sigh* Great, thanks...
Tsukasa: Seeing everybody having fun and enjoying themselves really is a sight to behold.
Ichika: Huh?
Tsukasa: A thought crossed my mind today. About how wonderful it is to see so many people smiling and laughing.
Tsukasa: Alright! Once I get home, I'll put on my new shoes and go for a run!
Tsukasa: I need to keep building up my stamina if I'm going to make more people smile!
Ichika: Okay, good luck!
Honami: Oh, look at the time. I think we can use that studio now.
Ichika: Yeah. We should start heading over.
Tsukasa: Ah, you have practice today. I'm sorry I kept you for so long.
Tsukasa: Well then, do your best! Farewell!
Saki: Bye bye! See you at home!
Miku: <It was nice to hear such a fun story, wasn't it?>
Ichika: Yeah, it was. He definitely seemed to be enjoying things as well.
Shiho: But we need to hurry over to the studio if we're gonna make our reservation.
Honami: Right...! We should run if we don't want to lose any time.
Ichika: Okay!
Saki: Great work, everyone!
Ichika: Nice work! For some reason, I felt really good during today's practice...
Honami: I also seemed to play better than usual on the drums.
Miku: <Yes, you all played with great energy.>
Saki: Wait, we did? Woohoo!
Shiho: Miku's right. We got off to a really good start today. Let's do our best to keep this up.
Honami: Then, see you all tomorrow. Nice work today, everyone.
Saki: Bye bye!
Miku: <Thank you for today, Ichika.>
Miku: <I'm really grateful about you letting me tag along to spectate. I'm so glad I did...>
Ichika: Hehe. Me too. You were right. This day ended up being more special than I initially expected.
Ichika: Oh, it's from my mom... “Could you grab some soy sauce at the store on your way home?”...?
Ichika: The supermarket's a bit out of the way, but okay...
Miku: <Looks like your special day's getting a slight extension.>
Ichika: I'm not sure running an errand counts.
Miku: <Really? I think it's a meaningful mission.>
Ichika: A mission...? I'm not Tsukasa...
Ichika: Huh...?
Miku: <What's wrong, Ichika?>
Ichika: Over there. That looks like...
Ichika: Kanade! Ena!
